== Prep ==

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}.

Pick the @mint{1}(stalks discarded, leaves picked) and roughly chop.

Roughly chop the @black olives{30}. Crumble the @feta cheese{100}.

== Bulgur ==

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a medium #saucepan{} on a medium-high heat.

When hot, add the @onion{}(chopped), cook stirring occasionally until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add half of the garlic and cook stirring frequently for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120}, @chicken stock paste{10} and @water{240}.

Bring to the boil. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and set aside for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Chicken ==

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a large #frying pan{} over a medium-high heat.

When hot add the @British chicken thighs{210} and cook stirring occasionally until browned all over, ~{6-7%minutes}.

When browned add the @honey{1}, @smoked paprika{1}, the remaining garlic, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and a splash of @water{splash}.

Cook stirring frequently until the chicken is glazed, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{} and gently stir through the baby plum tomatoes, olives, mint and half of the feta.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the bulgur between your bowls and top with the glazed chicken.

Crumble over the remaining feta and enjoy!